\subsection{Looking up one tutorial by ID}

The CLI should fail early with a useful error when the user asks for a
missing tutorial.

<<tutorial catalog methods>>=
def get_tutorial(self, tutorial_id: str) -> Tutorial:
    """Return the loaded tutorial with the given ID."""

    tutorial = self.tutorials_by_id.get(tutorial_id)
    if tutorial is not None:
        return tutorial

    available = ", ".join(item.id for item in self.tutorials)
    raise KeyError(
        f"Unknown tutorial {tutorial_id!r}. Available tutorials: {available}"
    )
@

