\section{Locating packaged built-in tutorials}

The standalone command should work without any extra setup, so the
package also ships a small set of Markdown tutorials.  We keep them as
ordinary files under [[src/tutorial/tutorials/]] rather than embedding
them as opaque resources.  That keeps their paths stable for resume logic
and for review output that wants to remember where a tutorial came from.

The built-ins also have a deliberate learning order:
\begin{description}
\item[[[using-tutorials]]]
  teaches how interactive runs behave.
\item[[[shell-basics]]]
  supplies the shell and editor skills needed for authoring.
\item[[[writing-tutorials]]]
  then builds on those earlier two tutorials.
\end{description}

