\section{Optional per-step metadata blocks}

Most of the step body should stay ordinary Markdown.  Validation rules,
hints, and editor-step configuration are the exception, so we reserve a
small leading code fence with the language tag [[tutorial-step]] for that
metadata.

<<constants>>=
STEP_METADATA_FENCE = "```tutorial-step"
@

<<functions>>=
def step_metadata_and_instructions(section_body: str) -> tuple[dict, str]:
    """Return ``(metadata, instructions)`` for one step body."""

    stripped_body = section_body.strip()
    lines = stripped_body.splitlines()
    if not lines or lines[0].strip() != STEP_METADATA_FENCE:
        return {}, stripped_body

    for index, line in enumerate(lines[1:], start=1):
        if line.strip() == "```":
            metadata = yaml.safe_load("\n".join(lines[1:index])) or {}
            if not isinstance(metadata, dict):
                raise ValueError("Tutorial step metadata must be a YAML mapping.")
            instructions = "\n".join(lines[index + 1 :]).strip()
            return metadata, instructions

    raise ValueError("Tutorial step metadata is missing its closing ``` fence.")
