\section{Fingerprinting one tutorial file}

Resuming an unfinished run only makes sense if the tutorial definition is
still the same as when the run began.  A file digest gives the runner a
small, stable identity check.

<<functions>>=
def build_source_digest(text: str) -> str:
    """Return a stable digest for one tutorial source file."""

    return hashlib.sha256(text.encode("utf-8")).hexdigest()
